plotText.plainText: In a wacky Rhode Island town, a dysfunctional family strives to cope with everyday life as they are thrown from one crazy scenario to another.

caption.plainText: Seth Green, Mila Kunis, Alex Borstein, and Seth MacFarlane in Family Guy (1999)

image.caption: Seth Green, Mila Kunis, Alex Borstein, and Seth MacFarlane in Family Guy (1999)

items.plot: After drinking too much at a stag party and falling asleep at work, Peter loses his job, signs up for welfare, and gets more money than expected.

items.titleText: I Never Met the Dead Man

image.caption: Lacey Chabert and Seth MacFarlane in Family Guy (1999)

items.plot: Peter goes into shock after he disables the entire Quahog cable system while giving Meg driving lessons; Stewie plots to rid the world of broccoli.

image.caption: Seth Green, Mila Kunis, Alex Borstein, and Seth MacFarlane in Family Guy (1999)

items.plot: Peter tries to make the best of a bad situation after he ruins Lois's plans for Stewie's birthday party; Meg's new friend tries to recruit her into a cult.

image.caption: Alex Borstein and Seth MacFarlane in Family Guy (1999)

items.plot: Under house arrest, Peter transforms the basement into a bar, where Lois' singing becomes the main attraction.

image.caption: Seth MacFarlane and Patrick Warburton in Family Guy (1999)

items.plot: Peter becomes very jealous, when his handi-capable new neighbor turns out to be the new star player on the toy company's softball team.
A chance encounter with a prune smoothie puts in motion a series of events that ultimately allows Peter to accept Chris' artistic side.
Brian's life is on the line after he refuses to be treated like a dog.
